article.headline: Bryant 59, Quinnipiac 50
article.story: NEW YORK -- Cecil Gresham scored 21 points to lead Bryant to a 59-50 victory over Quinnipiac in the consolation game of the Tyler Ugolyn-Columbia Classic on Saturday. Host Columbia met Maryland-Baltimore County in the championship game. Quinnipiac (2-2) got 15 points from James Feldeine, while Justin Rutty scored 13 and James Johnson 11. Feldeine led a second half surge that brought the Bobcats who trailed by as much as 14, to within 2 at 51-49 with 2:42 left. Bryant (2-3) expanded a 31-25 halftime lead to 41-27 on Chris Birrell's steal and layup with 15:58 remaining, but Feldeine hit another layup that began the Bobcats rally. With Bryant ahead by 2, Barry Latham sank a jump shot to make it 53-49 and, after a foul shot by Jeremy Baker, Jerrann Wright hit another jumper to give Bryant a 55-50 lead. Birrell scored 10 points for Bryant while Baker had 10 rebounds for Quinnipiac, which enjoyed a 39-25 rebounding advantage.
